
[1]grim

   GRIM, a. [L. fremo; Eng. grumble, rumble.]

   1. Fierce; ferocious; impressing terror; frightful; horrible; as a grim
   look; a grim face; grim war.

   2. Ugly; ill looking.

   3. Sour; crabbed peevish; surly.
